      "content": "that makes sense, but it feels like the bank is kinda winning in the beginning. like, if i look at a $400k loan at 6.5%, for the first few years it seems like almost nothing actually goes to the house itself, it just goes to interest. it feels like these costs are just constantly nibbling away at my equity before i can even get a foothold. can u show me some rough numbers for a $400k loan to show how much of a single monthly payment actually goes to principal in year 1 vs year 25?",
