      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just frustrating. it feels like the interest is this hidden thing that just hangs around your money, taking little bites out of it every month. like, how is it even possible for a bank to design a system where you basically pay them for decades before you actually own much of your own home? it feels almost malicious how they structure it to take most of the value upfront.",
